						               													<description>Whether in the big city or in the country, you'll find planting beds everywhere. What could be better than growing a plant from a letter, watching it grow, and then proudly looking at the words you've grown yourself?&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Words Querbeet - the somewhat different dice game! Ideal for all those who love to fiddle with letters. Roll the three letter dice and enter at least one of the diced letters into your crossword grid. Whether vertically or horizontally - the goal is to put together as many valid words as possible. With a bit of luck, the joker is rolled and you have the free choice of letters.&amp;#10;Four exciting game variants are waiting to be discovered by you - and you can also garden alone. But now into the rubber boots and off into the bed!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The game principle:&amp;#10;The game is played with three letter cubes. In each round, at least one of the diced letters must be entered into the crossword grid on your own game sheet. Jokers allow tactical decisions. The player who assembles the most meaningful words vertically and horizontally wins.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;mdash;description from the publisher&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
